why does consumer reprocess old messaes after restart?

what's happening
the consumer process messages normally and logs success.
after a restart (deploy, crash, scale) if re-reads older offsets

impact:
	duplicate DB writes
	repeated emails/sms
	replayed bussiness events

this always means offst commits are wrong or missing

why this happens (real produciton causes)
offsets not committed

enable.auto.commit=false
maual commitsync() missing
 -> kafka thinks messages were never processes

auto-commit interval too large
	app crashes before next auto-commit
	-> messages in that window replay(crash window)

commit timing is wrong
commit before processing -> messages loss

incorrect async commits
commitsync() can overwrite newer offsets
 -> offst goes backward -> old messages replay

large batch commit at end
crash mid-batch -> entire batch reprocessed

commit before db write
	offset committed db fails
	-> kafka won't resend -> data loss in db

commit inside try block only
	exception skips commit
	-> messages replay after restart.

consumer group deleted/expired
kafka forget offsets
	-> consumer starts from earliest

what's actually happening(siple view)
consumer process messages
	|
offsets not committed properly
	|
crash/restart
	|
kafka belives consumer stopped earlier
	|
consumer starts from old offset -> replay

